The paper deals with a path planning problem in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The procedure described in the abstract involves adding and removing sets from a collection, which suggests a dynamic data structure (cs.DS) is being used. The sets being added are convex, which is a common property studied in computational geometry. The problem of separating two points with a collection of convex sets is related to geometric range searching (cs.DM) and geometric graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the use of the Ackermann function in the time complexity analysis suggests a focus on algorithmic efficiency and complexity theory (cs.SI).
